Criminals have struck again at Edendale Crossing. On Wednesday afternoon, Midlands Builders Supply was robbed by armed robbers. According to Pietermaritzburg police spokesperson Sergeant Sifiso Gwala, two unknown men wearing masks entered the shop and went straight to the office where the owner was. “They pointed a firearm at the owner and demanded cellphone and cash. They took an undisclosed amount of money and fled the scene. No one was injured during the whole incident. Police are investigating a case of business robbery. No one has been arrested,” he said.